RECORD_ID — Unique identifier for the outbound call record generated by the vendor system.
CONTACT_INFO_TYPE — Type of contact information used for outreach, such as home phone, mobile phone, or other contact method.
RECORD_TYPE — Classification of the outbound record within the vendor dialing platform.
DIAL_SCHED_TIME — Scheduled time for the outbound call attempt in the vendor dialing system.
CALL_TIME — System-generated call time value captured by the vendor platform.
DAILY_FROM — Earliest time of day when calls may be placed to the member.
DAILY_TILL — Latest time of day when calls may be placed to the member.
TZ_DBID — Identifier of the timezone associated with the member or call record in the vendor system.
CAMPAIGN_ID — Identifier of the outreach campaign associated with the call record.
AGENT_ID — Identifier of the agent or automated process that handled the call attempt.
CHAIN_ID — Identifier representing the call chain or dialing workflow associated with the record.
CHAIN_N — Sequence number of the record within the dialing chain.
GROUP_ID — Identifier of the vendor-defined group associated with the campaign or call record.
APP_ID — Identifier of the application or dialing platform used to manage the call record.
TREATMENTS — Outreach treatment, script, or messaging configuration applied to the member record.
MEDIA_REF — Reference identifier for the media, script, or communication asset used during the outreach attempt.
SWITCH_ID — Identifier of the switch or telephony system used to place the call.
